30{
31 return true;

34bool ValidateBlendEquationSeparatei(const Context *context,
35 GLuint buf,
36 GLenum modeRGB,
37 GLenum modeAlpha)
38{
39 if (buf >= static_cast<GLuint>(context->getCaps().maxDrawBuffers))
40 {
41 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kExceedsMaxDrawBuffers);
42 return false;
43 }
44
45 if (!ValidateBlendEquationSeparate(context, modeRGB, modeAlpha))
46 {
47 // error already generated
48 return false;
49 }
50
51 return true;
52}
53
54bool ValidateBlendEquationi(const Context *context, GLuint buf, GLenum mode)

62 if (!ValidateBlendEquation(context, mode))

64 // error already generated
65 return false;
66 }
67
68 return true;
69}

126bool ValidateCopyImageSubData(const Context *context,
127 GLuint srcName,
128 GLenum srcTarget,
129 GLint srcLevel,
130 GLint srcX,
131 GLint srcY,
132 GLint srcZ,
133 GLuint dstName,
134 GLenum dstTarget,
135 GLint dstLevel,
136 GLint dstX,
137 GLint dstY,
138 GLint dstZ,
139 GLsizei srcWidth,
140 GLsizei srcHeight,
141 GLsizei srcDepth)
142{
143 if (context->getClientVersion() < ES_3_2)
144 {
145 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kES32Required);
146 return false;
147 }
148
149 return ValidateCopyImageSubDataBase(context, srcName, srcTarget, srcLevel, srcX, srcY, srcZ,
150 dstName, dstTarget, dstLevel, dstX, dstY, dstZ, srcWidth,
151 srcHeight, srcDepth);
152}

183bool ValidateDisablei(const Context *context, GLenum target, GLuint index)
184{
185 switch (target)
186 {
187 case GL_BLEND:
188 if (index >= static_cast<GLuint>(context->getCaps().maxDrawBuffers))
189 {
190 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kIndexExceedsMaxDrawBuffer);
191 return false;
192 }
193 break;
194 default:
195 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
196 return false;
197 }
198 return true;
199}

201bool ValidateDrawElementsBaseVertex(const Context *context,
202 PrimitiveMode mode,
203 GLsizei count,
204 DrawElementsType type,
205 const void *indices,
206 GLint basevertex)
207{
208 if (!context->getExtensions().drawElementsBaseVertexAny())
209 {
210 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kExtensionNotEnabled);
211 return false;
212 }
213
214 return ValidateDrawElementsCommon(context, mode, count, type, indices, 1);
215}
216
217bool ValidateDrawElementsInstancedBaseVertex(const Context *context,
218 PrimitiveMode mode,
219 GLsizei count,
220 DrawElementsType type,
221 const void *indices,
222 GLsizei instancecount,
223 GLint basevertex)
224{
225 if (!context->getExtensions().drawElementsBaseVertexAny())
226 {
227 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kExtensionNotEnabled);
228 return false;
229 }
230
231 return ValidateDrawElementsInstancedBase(context, mode, count, type, indices, instancecount);
232}
233
234bool ValidateDrawRangeElementsBaseVertex(const Context *context,
235 PrimitiveMode mode,
236 GLuint start,
237 GLuint end,
238 GLsizei count,
239 DrawElementsType type,
240 const void *indices,
241 GLint basevertex)
242{
243 if (!context->getExtensions().drawElementsBaseVertexAny())
244 {
245 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kExtensionNotEnabled);
246 return false;
247 }
248
249 if (end < start)
250 {
251 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidElementRange);
252 return false;
253 }
254
255 if (!ValidateDrawElementsCommon(context, mode, count, type, indices, 0))
256 {
257 return false;
258 }
259
260 // Skip range checks for no-op calls.
261 if (count <= 0)
262 {
263 return true;
264 }
265
266 return true;
267}

333bool ValidateGetPointerv(const Context *context, GLenum pname, void *const *params)
334{
335 Version clientVersion = context->getClientVersion();
336
337 if ((clientVersion == ES_1_0) || (clientVersion == ES_1_1))
338 {
339 switch (pname)
340 {
341 case GL_VERTEX_ARRAY_POINTER:
342 case GL_NORMAL_ARRAY_POINTER:
343 case GL_COLOR_ARRAY_POINTER:
344 case GL_TEXTURE_COORD_ARRAY_POINTER:
345 case GL_POINT_SIZE_ARRAY_POINTER_OES:
346 return true;
347 default:
348 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidPointerQuery);
349 return false;
350 }
351 }
352 else if (clientVersion == ES_3_2)
353 {
354 switch (pname)
355 {
356 case GL_DEBUG_CALLBACK_FUNCTION:
357 case GL_DEBUG_CALLBACK_USER_PARAM:
358 return true;
359 default:
360 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidPointerQuery);
361 return false;
362 }
363 }
364 else
365 {
366 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kES1or32Required);
367 return false;
368 }
369}

531bool ValidateTexBuffer(const Context *context,
532 TextureType target,
533 GLenum internalformat,
534 BufferID buffer)
535{
536 if (context->getClientVersion() < ES_3_2)
537 {
538 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kES32Required);
539 return false;
540 }
541
542 return ValidateTexBufferBase(context, target, internalformat, buffer);
543}
